ù Introduction

Grep lets you search multiple files for a string of text.


®B¯Features:®/B¯

    ù ...Under Construction... (and yes, i suppose that's a feature <g>)

    ù Remembers the results of the last 10 searches; Back/Forward commands let
      you browse the previous results (similar to Internet Explorer's
      Back/Forward commands for browsing web pages).
    ù Optional window shows the lines surrounding each matching line; this
      window can be scrolled.
    ù "Refresh" command re-does the search, to reflect any changes made since
      the search was last performed.
    ù Can automatically load all files with matches.
    ù Performs searches in the background, while you continue editing.


